---
# Build-time TRANSPARENCY projection of this Tell's judge-side per-poll registry
# (_data/constitutions/<pile>/<poll>.json): a small, cacheable, PUBLIC list of which polls
# this Tell governs and by what rule (question, type, options, accept_writein, guidance,
# lifecycle). Nothing private lives here; guidance is already shown to respondents.
#
# It is NOT in the respondent path. A poll is self-contained in its (signed) QR and is
# intentionally unbacked — the landing renders from the QR, not from here (see
# docs/per-poll-registry.md). This file exists to make a Tell's governance legible, and is
# the natural seam for a later, made-public list used in cross-node discovery.
#
# No network IO at build. Shape: a flat array of poll objects, each keyed by {pile, poll}.
layout: null
permalink: /polls.json
---
{%- comment -%}
  site.data.constitutions is a hash {pile => {poll => config}} (Jekyll namespaces nested
  _data dirs). Liquid has no array push and nested forloop.last is unreliable across two
  levels, so we emit each object with a "|||" terminator, split, then join with commas —
  Ruby's split drops the trailing empty, giving valid JSON with no dangling comma.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture rows -%}
{%- for pile in site.data.constitutions -%}
{%- for poll in pile[1] -%}
{%- assign c = poll[1] -%}
{"pile":{{ c.pile | jsonify }},"poll":{{ c.poll | jsonify }},"type":{{ c.type | jsonify }},"text":{{ c.text | jsonify }},"options":{{ c.options | jsonify }},"accept_writein":{{ c.accept_writein | jsonify }},"guidance":{{ c.guidance | jsonify }}{% if c.lifecycle %},"lifecycle":{{ c.lifecycle | jsonify }}{% endif %}}|||
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}
{%- assign items = rows | split: "|||" -%}
[{{ items | join: "," }}]
